cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.NA, cs.IT, cs.SI 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with the reconstruction of fiber tracts using diffusion magnetic resonance imaging (dMRI) data. The use of regularization terms to encourage spatial coherence and data fidelity also suggests that it could belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The optimization algorithm used in the paper, block coordinate descent, is commonly used in numerical analysis and optimization (cs.NA), which could also be a likely sub-category. The use of directional information and interaction between neighbor voxels suggests that it could belong to the information theory (cs.IT) or signal processing (cs.SI) sub-categories.
